    <cas:Sofa xmi:id="1" sofaNum="1" sofaID="_InitialView" mimeType="text" sofaString="4 LASSA FEVER 4.1 In the reporting Week 6 (4 – 10 February, 2019), thirty-seven new confirmediI cases were reported from Edo (10), Ondo (12), Ebonyi (4), Plateau (4), Taraba (3), Benue (1), Gombe (1), Rivers (1) and Kebbi (1) States with ten new deaths in Edo (2), Ondo (2), Ebonyi (4) and Plateau (2) States. 4.2 From 1st January – 10th February 2019, a total of 947 suspectedi cases have been reported from 20 States. Of these, 324 were confirmed positive, 3 probable and 620 negatives (not a case) 4.3 Since the onset of the 2019 outbreak, there have been 67 deaths among confirmed cases. Case Fatality Rate in confirmed cases is 21.3% 4.4 Twenty states have recorded at least one confirmed case across 54 LGAs (Edo, Ondo, Bauchi, Nasarawa, Ebonyi, Plateau, Taraba, FCT, Adamawa, Gombe, Kaduna, Kwara, Benue, Rivers, Kogi, Enugu, Imo, Delta, Oyo &amp; Kebbi) and remain active."/>
